# Hyrenet — TLS terminator + wildcard preview (production, in front of the orchestrator)
#
# This is the deploy-time piece of Phase 2 that cannot be proven on localhost (it
# needs the real assess.hyrenet.in domain + DNS). It is the production analogue of
# v1's `*.preview.localhost` trick: Caddy terminates TLS and reverse-proxies every
# request — API, candidate preview vhost, and the Vite HMR WebSocket — to the single
# orchestrator port. The host-token preview scheme (token = left-most host label)
# already works unchanged behind TLS; nothing about preview.go changes.
#
# Why Caddy and not just an ALB: Caddy gets a real *.preview.hyrenet.in wildcard
# cert from Let's Encrypt via the DNS-01 challenge automatically (ALB needs an ACM
# cert you provision separately, and ALB host-based routing to one target group is
# fine too — see deploy/README for the ALB variant). For a single node, Caddy is
# the least moving parts.
#
# DNS (one-time, at your provider):
#   A    assess.hyrenet.in          -> <node public IP>
#   A    *.preview.assess.hyrenet.in -> <node public IP>   (wildcard, for previews)
#
# Run the orchestrator with the public-facing names so the URLs it mints are right:
#   AUTH_ENABLED=true \
#   PREVIEW_DOMAIN=preview.assess.hyrenet.in \
#   PREVIEW_PORT=443 \
#   SANDBOX_RUNTIME=runsc \
#   LISTEN_ADDR=127.0.0.1:8090 \
#   DATABASE_URL=... go run ./cmd/orchestrator
#
# The DNS-01 challenge needs your provider's API token; this example uses Cloudflare.
# Swap the dns block for your provider (caddy-dns modules) or use ACM+ALB instead.

{
	# email for Let's Encrypt expiry notices
	email ops@hyrenet.in
}

# --- Control-plane API + dashboard origin ---
assess.hyrenet.in {
	encode zstd gzip
	reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:8090 {
		# Stream dev-server + scoring output without buffering.
		flush_interval -1
	}
}

# --- Candidate preview vhost (wildcard) ---
# Matches <token>.<session>.preview.assess.hyrenet.in. The orchestrator reads the
# token from the host label and authorizes per-session; Caddy just needs the
# wildcard cert and to pass the Host header through (reverse_proxy does by default),
# including WebSocket upgrades for Vite HMR (also automatic).
*.preview.assess.hyrenet.in {
	tls {
		dns cloudflare {env.CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN}
	}
	reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:8090 {
		flush_interval -1
	}
}
